Excellent! I recommend getting as much water as possible out of the tofu before marinating. To do this: pat tofu dry, wrap in paper towels, and place it on top of a cloth towel with a heavy plate over it (you can leave it this way for hours,even store in the refrigerator overnight). I agree that the tofu is better when marinated overnight. Next time I will make a fresh batch of the sauce for the stir fry, since the sauce on my veggies was not nearly as flavorful as the marinade -- the tofu seemed to soak up most of the flavor. (I would use a double batch of sauce for the tofu and another double batch for the stir fry, especially if serving over rice.) I used peanut oil because of the high temp, too, and sprinkled corn starch on the tofu before frying which worked great -- thanks to others for the tips!

