Rating: 0
To the cook in North Carolina--I have worked with tofu plenty in the past, and a great way to get it crispy is as follows: press the tofu to remove most of the liquid (it helps if the tofu is extra firm), cut it into cubes and then simply shake it in a bag with some corn starch. Dust off the extra corn starch and cook the cubed tofu in very hot oil until LIGHTLY browned. The tofu will have a nice crispy texture. I hope this helps

