This was fabulous! First time we ever made tofu, and I couldn't have been more pleased. We made it exactly as written, except we used pre-sliced baby bella mushrooms because the grocery was out of shiitakes. I am definitely adding this to our rotation.

Rating: 3
This dish was fanstastic! And it's a perfect vegetarian dish for those who think they don't like "vegetarian food." It's good for a week day when you don't have much time to cook. I used string beans (cut into 1-inch pieces) instead of sugar snap peas to save a little bit of money, since fresh shiitakes can be a little pricy.

Rating: 3
This was good but I thought the flavor of the tofu was a bit bland and I will marinate overnight next time I make this. I also used peanut oil because of the high heat and probably a bit more than the recipe called for. If you like spicy foods it could also use a bit more heat, try adding additional red pepper flakes. All in all this was a good combination of flavors.

Rating: 4
Delicious and easy. Both my husband and I loved it, and good tofu recipes are hard to come by. The only modifications I made were as follows: I drained the tofu in a colander under a heavy can for a few minutes first; used peanut oil instead of vegetable oil because of the high heat, and added strips of red pepper at the same time as the sugar snaps for color. I also had to add a bit more oil after the mushrooms because they absorbed all the oil.